## DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW

### Primary Development Process
**Static File Development:**
```
1. Edit index.html directly in code editor
2. Open index.html in browser to preview
3. Test on multiple browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
4. Test responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)
5. Validate HTML/CSS using browser DevTools
6. Commit changes with descriptive messages
7. Push to GitHub (auto-deploys to GitHub Pages)
```

### Command Structure & Scripts

#### Development Commands
```bash
# Open in browser for testing
open index.html
# or
python3 -m http.server 8000  # Simple local server

# Validate HTML (if w3c validator installed)
# Visit: https://validator.w3.org/
```

#### Quality Assurance Commands
```bash
# Check browser console for JavaScript errors
# Use browser DevTools (F12)

# Test responsive design
# Use browser DevTools device toolbar (Cmd+Shift+M)

# Accessibility testing
# Use Lighthouse in Chrome DevTools
```

