## STATIC WEBSITE ARCHITECTURE

### Single-Page Design
**All content in index.html:**
```
- Header: Logo, theme toggle
- Hero: Main value proposition, CTA buttons
- Problem: Three crises being addressed
- Solution: How RideCareShare works
- Features: Key features grid
- How It Works: Step-by-step process
- Impact: Projected social impact
- Founder: Vadim's story and motivation
- Testimonials: Early user feedback
- Waitlist: Signup form
- Footer: Copyright, social media links
```

### Theme System
**Dark/Light mode toggle:**
```javascript
- CSS variables for theming (--bg-primary, --text-primary, etc.)
- localStorage persistence for user preference
- Smooth transitions between themes
- Accessible color contrast in both modes
```

### Social Media Integration
**Footer social links:**
```
- Facebook: https://facebook.com (to be updated with actual account)
- X (Twitter): https://twitter.com (to be updated with actual account)
- Instagram: https://instagram.com (to be updated with actual account)
- YouTube: https://youtube.com (to be updated with actual account)
```

---

## DATA & STATE MANAGEMENT

### Client-Side State
**Minimal state management:**
```javascript
- Theme preference: Stored in localStorage
- Waitlist form data: Captured and logged (awaiting email service integration)
- Smooth scroll: JavaScript for anchor link navigation
```

### No Database Required
This is a static landing page. Waitlist submissions will eventually integrate with an email service provider, but no database is needed for the website itself.

